    "Action Keys" : {

    },
    "Action kinds Docky will execute: built-in commands, AppleScript, and macOS menu-bar clicks. The first time an app-targeted AppleScript or menu-click action runs, macOS may prompt for Automation permission." : {

    },
    "Actions are menu items Docky injects into each tile's right-click menu. A catalog package ships a curated bundle of them; once it's loaded, every action it defines is automatically available on the matching tile type. Apps, folders, the Trash, the Launchpad, and the divider all get their own set, with no per-tile setup needed." : {
      "comment" : "A description of how actions are integrated into Docky.",
      "isCommentAutoGenerated" : true
    },
